main event: A brilliant object was observed on the western horizon in Aguada, Puerto Rico on July 23, 1965. The object moved north, made a semi-circle turn moving to the south, and then disappeared.
interesting points: The object seemed to change to an orange or reddish glow before disappearing.
The observer took photographs of the object.
The object made a humming sound when it rushed away.
The object was estimated to be moving at a speed of approximately 3,400 mph.
The observer had been studying astronomy and unusual sky phenomena, and believed the object may have been an unusual natural phenomenon.
